episodes.title: Stunning and Brave
episodes.plot: The boys show their respect for Caitlyn Jenner when a new principal makes them atone for a history of prejudice.

episodes.plot: Garrison decides he wants to build a wall to keep out all the undocumented immigrants.

episodes.plot: With the town of South Park gentrifying, Kenny decides to get a job at City Wok.

episodes.title: You're Not Yelping
episodes.plot: Cartman considers himself the top online restaurant reviewer in South Park.

episodes.title: Safe Space
episodes.plot: Cartman is victimised because of his body weight.

episodes.title: Tweek x Craig
episodes.plot: The East Asian girls in school are drawing intimate pictures of Tweek and Craig.

episodes.title: Naughty Ninjas
episodes.plot: The ever more PC citizens of South Park decide that they no longer need a police force. As the first American town to get rid of their cops, they plan to celebrate their advanced sensibilities with a PC Carnival.

episodes.title: Sponsored Content
episodes.plot: PC Principal's ideology is tested when the school newspaper writes about the PC Fraternity. Meanwhile ads slowly consume the Internet news, as Garrison participates in the political debate with Hilary Clinton.

episodes.title: Truth and Advertising
episodes.plot: Principal Victoria and Mr. Garrison are back in town trying to stop PC. Meanwhile Jimmy tries to uncover the secret of Leslie.

episodes.title: PC Principal Final Justice
episodes.plot: PC Principal travels around the world, destroying gentrifying districts. The town of South Park arms itself just as the gun show comes into town , Jimmy is held captive by Nathan, Kyle protects Leslie and the final showdown will start.
